00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:11.800
when you're down at the beach.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:13.120
Let's jump right in.

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:16.260
When you pull up to the beach it's not alway convenient

00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:18.720
to take your car keys with you, but you wont find lockers

00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:20.720
at the beach and you can't take your keys with you in the ocean

00:00:20.720 --> 00:00:22.240
either, so what do you do?

00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:25.400
Try looping a long sturdy blade of grass through your keychain, tying

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:26.540
it off to form a ring.

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.020
Then press the loop into one of the top treads of

00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:30.660
your tire, holding it in place with a small pebble.

00:00:30.780 --> 00:00:33.980
Flip the keys back so they dangle behind the tire

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:36.380
and they'll be out of sight, out of mind, and off the ground as well.

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:40.320
So they won't get exposed to moisture if it rains while you are gone.

00:00:40.940 --> 00:00:43.100
Now if you are in a hurry and don't have the time or patience

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:45.160
to jury-rig a hook, you could simply toss your keys

00:00:45.160 --> 00:00:47.160
behind one of your tires instead.

00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:48.780
I've been using this trick for years,

00:00:48.780 --> 00:00:52.260
and as long as you do it discreetly, no one will have any idea your keys are even back there.

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:56.200
So go have fun! Play without the worry of losing or destroying your keys at the beach.

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:00.260
because when you come back, you should find they're stashed exactly where you left them.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:03.440
The next time you want to go snorkeling

00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:06.400
but don't have a safe place for your phone, keys, and cash,

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:09.360
you can use a clean baby diaper to stash all your valuables instead.

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:11.980
Use the sticky tabs to hold the bundle together,

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:15.760
and to the untrained eye, it's just a used diaper that nobody wants to touch.

00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:18.740
By the way, if you set it down next to your towel and flip-flops,

00:01:18.740 --> 00:01:21.140
it'll be a lot less likely to get thrown away by accident.

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:24.360
Now if you want to go one step further,

00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:28.760
try opening a pack of chocolate spread and rubbing some along the inside flap of the diaper.

00:01:28.760 --> 00:01:31.760
This will make your decoy diaper look authentically used

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:34.460
and should be enough to discourage any would-be beach thieves

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:35.820
from finding your stuff.

00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:38.940
Have you ever stopped to unravel a poopy diaper lying at the beach?

00:01:38.940 --> 00:01:41.320
Of course you haven't! And nobody else will either.

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:45.140
To prove this point, I left mine exposed and unattended for over an hour,

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:48.400
