00:01:49.820 --> 00:01:52.740
When you're bodysurfing, splashing in the waves, or out for a little swim,

00:01:52.740 --> 00:01:55.640
you may suddenly notice that your ears don't feel normal anymore.

00:01:56.240 --> 00:01:59.940
The feeling of water trapped in your ears is uncomfortable, and makes it difficult to hear.

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:04.040
Point the affected ear to the ground and jump up and down with a few sharp jolts.

00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:07.220
You should hear the water tension break and clear out almost instantly.

00:02:07.220 --> 00:02:09.840
The key here is in the sudden jolts at the end.

00:02:09.840 --> 00:02:14.180
Do the same thing with the other ear, and you should feel cleared up and back to normal as easy as that.

00:02:14.660 --> 00:02:18.240
Now some people suggest that blowing up a balloon will have the exact same effect.

00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:19.800
